Anterior border of carapace ( Fig. 2A ; Chen 1985 : fig. 5, as
E. sexdentata
) with slender to broad, nearly triangular, distally acute, straight outer orbital teeth, reaching or nearly reaching shorter frontal teeth. Frontal teeth nearly triangular, equal or nearly-equal. Orbital sinuses broad, U-shaped, nearly symmetrical (inner margins nearly straight, outer margins J-shaped) or symmetrical; lateral frontal sinuses U-shaped; median frontal sinus V-shaped, as wide as lateral frontal sinuses but narrower than orbital sinuses.

Anterior border of endostome ( Fig. 2B ; Chen 1985 : fig. 6a, as
E. sexdentata
) lies below posteri- or border of antennular fossae of basal antennular articles.

